<h2>smoothtail: Smooth Estimation of GPD Shape Parameter</h2>
<p>Given independent and identically distributed observations X(1), ..., X(n) from a Generalized Pareto distribution with shape parameter gamma in [-1,0], offers several estimates to compute estimates of gamma. The estimates are based on the principle of replacing the order statistics by quantiles of a distribution function based on a log&ndash;concave density function. This procedure is justified by the fact that the GPD density is log&ndash;concave for gamma in [-1,0].</p>
